The paper deals with the complexity of polytopes related to a wide class of problems and graphs, which suggests that it could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The use of MSO logic and treewidth in the paper suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) categories. The study of geometric tools and polytopes suggests that it could belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories.
